    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-13T10:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-13T10:14:00-05:00" n="385"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/340.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-13T10:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Official report dated February 10, 10 p.m., says consular officers unable to
                    secure zone for the protection of noncombatants. Consulates and neutral property
                    will be respected as asylum by the combatants. Shall I further report?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goding</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
